      • setStorageSpecs

      • setVmServiceSpec

        public InstancesTypes.UpdateSpec.Builder setVmServiceSpec(InstancesTypes.VMServiceSpec vmServiceSpec)
        VM Service specification associated with the namespace.

        NOTE: Any change in the VM Service Content Libraries associated with the namespace will be updated and merged with the the Content Library list in VM Image Service. If {UpdateSpec#contentLibraries} is unset, the Content Libraries specified here will be honored if no writable Content Libraries are removed from the current Content Library list by Instances.get(java.lang.String) method, otherwise InvalidArgument error will be thrown.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. If null, the Content Libraries get configured based on the values in {UpdateSpec#contentLibraries}, if it is specified.
        Parameters:
        vmServiceSpec - New value for the property.

      • setContentLibraries

        public InstancesTypes.UpdateSpec.Builder setContentLibraries(java.util.List<InstancesTypes.ContentLibrarySpec> contentLibraries)
        List of Content Libraries used by the VM Image Service. This list refers to existing Content Libraries in vSphere inventory.

        The Content Libraries specified in {VMServiceSpec#contentLibraries} will also be included in this list but will be read-only by default to users.

        If the same Content Library is present both here and in {VMServiceSpec#contentLibraries}, then:

        • The Content Library is only surfaced to users once.
        • The settings here are honored.

        NOTE: Any change in the VM Image Service Content Libraries associated with the namespace will be updated and merged with the Content Library list in VMServiceSpec. If {UpdateSpec#vmServiceSpec#contentLibraries} is unset, the Content Libraries specified here will be honored and the Content Libraries removed from the current Content Library list by Instances.get(java.lang.String) method will also be removed from VM Service.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null, the Content Libraries get configured based on the values in {UpdateSpec#vmServiceSpec#contentLibraries}, if it is specified.
        Parameters:
        contentLibraries - New value for the property.
